    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "@minrk: I actually agree with both approaches: things like pylab_activate should probably flush right away just to be safe, and we should also have a flush right at the end of the IPKernelApp startup, to hand off things in a clean state.  I can look into the code tomorrow, but if you have a minute just push those small changes up right away.  I'd rather not add flushing on every block execute at the start; since we do flush at the end, it's superfluous on all but the first.\n"
